        <p class="text-base-content/70 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3">
          This haunting song captures the feeling of watching situations spiral completely out of control—like a runaway 
          train that no one can stop. The narrator observes the chaos but recognizes their powerlessness to intervene. 
          This perfectly embodies strategic detachment: recognizing when something is beyond your control and choosing 
          not to throw yourself in front of the metaphorical runaway train.
        </p>
        <p class="text-base-content/70 text-sm leading-relaxed">
          Sometimes the wisest action is to step back and watch, rather than getting caught up in the momentum of 
          someone else's disaster. The song's melancholy reminds us that detachment doesn't mean we don't care—it 
          means we're smart enough not to become casualties.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-secondary/5 to-primary/5 p-6 rounded-box border border-secondary/20 backdrop-blur-sm">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-secondary mb-3">Common Mistakes to Avoid:</h4>
        <ul class="text-base-content/70 text-sm space-y-2">
          <li>• <strong class="text-secondary">False Neutrality:</strong> Claiming to be neutral while secretly taking sides</li>
          <li>• <strong class="text-secondary">Detachment as Apathy:</strong> Confusing strategic withdrawal with not caring</li>
          <li>• <strong class="text-secondary">Information Hoarding:</strong> Using your neutral position to gather gossip for entertainment</li>
          <li>• <strong class="text-secondary">Moral Grandstanding:</strong> Breaking neutrality to demonstrate your values publicly</li>
        </ul>
